From: "Reiter, Paul I." <ipr1@CIDVBI2.EM.CDC.GOV>
via: mosquito-l <mosquito-l@iastate.edu>
Subject: Re: Aedes albopictus/Ae. aegypti
Date: Mon, 04 Mar 96 10:23:00 EST
Dra Dalva Wanderley, Secretaria de Estado da Saude, Superintendencia de
controle de Endemias, Rua Paula Souza, 166, CEP 01027-000, Sao Paulo is the
person to contact. She is in charge of Ae aegypti control in Sao Paulo
state, one of the most effective organizations of its kind in the Americas.
She has lots of good quality data on the albopictus saga, and I am sure
there are publications.
I am not advocating importing albo to these shores! I have little doubt it
will not need our help to arrive, sooner or later.
As far as I remember, in Singapore, about 50% of indoor infestations are
albopictus, not aegypti.
Paul Reiter
